              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "column",
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": ""
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "image",
              "url": "https://drive.google.com/file/d/1LUvOamgX0yt2c6bLF39o-M6gYAsSu-2P/view?usp=sharing",
              "caption": "Skeleton of the Dem Bow Riddim from Marshall (2009) ",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": ""
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "children": [
                {
                  "text": ""
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "\"Dancehall and hip-hop have tended to travel together, heard outside their principal sites of production as two sides of the same coin\" (Marshall, 2009 p. 25). Dancehall made its way to San Juan not from Kingston, but from New York. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Connected with the growth and influence of New York's Jamaican community in the 1980s, by the 1990s, dancehall reggae had worked its way into the sets of hip-hop DJs and became a culturally charged feature of the New York soundscape. These riddims would later be deeply incorporated into the underground recordings of the early 1990s that laid the musical foundations for reggaeton. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "includes": [
        "media",
        "annotations",
        "label",
